title: Neal Francis – Changes (live for The Current)
description:
Chicago musician Neal Francis visited The Current studio while on tour in support of his album "In Plain Sight." During the session, he and his band performed the song "Changes" from Francis's 2019 debut release. Watch the full performance above.  

Band members
Neal Francis – vocals, piano
Kellen Boersma – guitar
Mike Starr – bass
Collin O’Brien – drums

title: Manchester Orchestra – two acoustic performances (live for The Current)
description:
In late August, Atlanta-based band Manchester Orchestra visited the Upper Midwest, where they performed as part of The Current’s Music on-a-Stick show at the Minnesota State Fair Grandstand. The show was notoriously cut short due to a sudden burst of severe weather, but not before Manchester Orchestra got in a good chunk of their set. 

Earlier in the day, Manchester Orchestra’s Andy Hull and Robert McDowell visited the MPR booth — aka Camp MPR — near the corner of Judson and Nelson, where they played acoustic versions of a couple of their songs. 

Songs performed:
00:00:00 Bed Head
00:03:58 The Gold 

Band members
Andy Hull - vocals, guitar
Robert McDowell - vocals, guitar
